description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, highly experienced practitioner to join the Trusts Eating Disorders Service&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This unique service provides treatment and care for individuals of all ages with an eating disorder and their families across the county of Dorset. It is predominantly a community-based service with treatment delivered in a variety of locations including the patient’s home. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will support the senior team by providing advanced clinical practice and leadership across the Eating Disorders Service. Their principal role is to work as a member of the multi-disciplinary eating disorders team, in partnership with people who have an eating disorder, their families and carers. To assess, plan and implement evidence-based interventions and high-quality care and to promote recovery from eating disorders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A key secondary role is to work closely with the Service Manager to develop and support staff and to improve the quality of care delivered. The post holder will hold their own caseload of community patients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Applicants must have extensive experience in the field of eating disorders, preferably with both child/adolescent and adult populations. They should also have proven leadership skills and experience of developing staff at an advanced level. The post holder will have the ability to work across organisational boundaries developing and maintaining multi-professional and multiagency relationships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in moving to Dorset, we also offer a generous relocation package of up to £5,000. For further details on relocation expenses please email dhc.careers@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments. This will only apply to candidates who are new to the Trust and not internal staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Lee Barker Job title: Clinical Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: lee.barker@nhs.net Telephone number: 01202 492147&lt;/p&gt;
